In the heat exchange process between the PV cell and the thin film (WD-ER unit), the Biot number is less than 0.01, which supports the lumped system analysis in the longitudinal direction, and most of the radiant energy is consumed for water desorption. Moreover, the solar thermal energy is uniformly supplied to the PV modules, enabling one-dimensional analysis. The well-known diffusion equation of desorbed water is Eq. (2)31, where mw is desorbed water mass (kg), K* is modified mass transfer coefficient (m/s), A is cross-sectional area (m2), Cs is concentration of water on the particle surface (kg/m3), and Cf is free stream concentration (kg/m3), respectively (This equation is defined as a pseudo first-order kinetic model35).2d(mw)dt=K*⋅A⋅(Cs−Cf)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
